1- Account setup & identity
    • Register with email or Google/Apple SSO
    • Select home country (US) and verify phone number
    • Complete identity verification (KYC lite — name, address, government ID photo)
    • Set preferred payout currency (USD) and connect US bank account via Plaid
    • Accept platform terms including tax responsibility disclaimer

2- Add a property
    • Select property country from supported list — app auto-assigns local payment processor
    • Enter property address using country-localised address fields (postcode format, state/province etc.)
    • Set property type (apartment, house, commercial), size, and bedrooms
    • Upload property photos (optional — for tenant-facing listing if using app discovery)
    • Confirm local currency for that property — locked to country (EUR for France, INR for India etc.)
    • Repeat for each property — unlimited properties, billing per unit from unit 2 onwards

3- Create a lease
Create a lease
    • Enter tenant details: name, email, phone (localised format)
    • Set lease start date, end date, and rent amount in local currency
    • Set rent due day (e.g. 1st of month) and grace period (e.g. 5 days)
    • Select payment frequency: monthly, fortnightly, weekly
    • Add security deposit amount and confirm it is held externally (app does not hold deposits)
    • Upload signed lease document PDF for record-keeping — stored against the lease
    • Send lease summary to tenant via email with payment setup instructions

4- Tenant onboarding & mandate
Tenant onboarding & mandate
    • Tenant receives email invite with localised payment setup link
    • Tenant completes local payment mandate (SEPA direct debit for EU, UPI autopay or NACH for India etc.)
    • Landlord receives confirmation that mandate is active
    • Landlord marks lease as 'active' — automated rent collection begins on first due date

5- Rent collection (automated)
Rent collection (automated)
    • App initiates local payment collection on due date via country processor
    • Landlord receives push notification and email: payment collected or failed
    • On success: rent logged in ledger with timestamp, amount, and FX rate snapshot
    • On failure: automated retry after 3 days; landlord notified of arrears after 2nd failure
    • Payment settles to landlord's in-country holding balance (not auto-transferred abroad)
    • Landlord can view running balance per property and per country at any time

6- Arrears & late payment management
Arrears & late payment management
    • App auto-sends localised late payment reminder to tenant on day 1 of arrears
    • Escalating reminder cadence: day 1, day 5, day 10 — tone escalates automatically
    • Landlord can manually send custom message to tenant from within the app
    • Landlord can log a manual payment (e.g. cash or bank transfer received outside app)
    • Landlord can mark debt as waived or disputed with a note
    • Outstanding arrears shown prominently on dashboard with days overdue

7- Maintenance requests
Maintenance requests
    • Tenant raises maintenance request via app with description and photos
    • Landlord receives notification and can accept, decline, or request more info
    • Landlord logs resolution notes and marks request closed
    • Full maintenance history stored per property — useful for deposit disputes
    • Landlord can attach contractor invoice or receipt to a closed request

8- Document management
Document management
    • Upload and store: lease agreements, inspection reports, insurance certificates, compliance docs
    • Documents organised by property and tagged by type
    • Share individual documents with tenant via secure link (time-limited download)
    • Receive tenant-uploaded documents (signed forms, ID copies, employer letters)
    • All documents retained for minimum 7 years per GDPR / local data law requirements

9- Financial dashboard & reporting
Financial dashboard & reporting
    • Unified dashboard showing all properties, all currencies, all balances
    • Monthly income summary per property in local currency and USD equivalent
    • FX rate logged at each payment — historical FX record for tax purposes
    • Annual income report per property — exportable as CSV and PDF for CPA
    • Outstanding balance tracker: what has been repatriated vs still in-country
    • Landlord manually logs repatriation events (amount, date, exchange rate used) for record

10- Lease renewal & end-of-tenancy
Lease renewal & end-of-tenancy
    • App alerts landlord 90, 60, and 30 days before lease expiry
    • Landlord can extend lease with new end date and optionally updated rent amount
    • Tenant notified of renewal terms — can accept or flag intention to vacate
    • At end of tenancy: landlord marks lease closed, final rent reconciled
    • Security deposit decision logged (returned, partially retained, disputed) — note only, app does not handle deposit money
    • Tenant access to app revoked 7 days after lease end — read-only payment history remains

11- Multi-property & portfolio view
Multi-property & portfolio view
    • All properties visible on single dashboard regardless of country or currency
    • Filter by country, currency, status (active, expiring, vacant, in arrears)
    • Aggregate totals shown in USD using last-known FX rates with refresh timestamp
    • Occupancy rate shown across portfolio
    • Net income trend chart by month across all properties combined

12- Notifications & communication   
Notifications & communication
    • Push, email, and in-app notifications for: payment received, payment failed, maintenance raised, lease expiring
    • In-app message thread per property — full conversation history with tenant
    • Broadcast message to all tenants in a property (for building-wide notices)
    • Landlord can set quiet hours — no notifications outside defined hours in their timezone
    • All communication timestamped and stored — admissible as correspondence record
